explanation: This solution uses a sliding window approach to check all substrings of the given string that have the same length as the total length of all words. It uses an unordered map to count the occurrences of each word in the words array and another unordered map to count the occurrences of each word in the current substring. If a word is not found in the wordCount map or its count exceeds the count in the wordCount map, the current substring is not a concatenated string and the loop breaks. If the loop completes without breaking, the current substring is a concatenated string and its starting index is added to the result.

